title: Man-Cave | Ireland's starting 15 against France has a few surprises in it
text:
There's a few surprises in the Irish starting lineup for Sunday clash with France, with Joe Schmidt ruffling a few feathers with his team selection.
Despite a few barnstorming displays from Iain Henderson, he's been placed on the bench with Devin Toner taking his starting birth, while Simon Zebo has been left out of the squad completely.
Zebo, who has performed brilliantly so far in the campaign, couldn't even find a spot among the replacements, and Cian Healy has reclaimed his no.1 jersey from Jack McGrath who starts from the subs bench
Here's the team for #FRAvIRE in #RWC2015 #ShoulderToShoulder pic.twitter.com/sQGPJTiNzb
